.SH "NAME"
idioms\-die \- die, printing a message to standard error if given
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\f(CR. \fBidioms\fP\fP
.sp
\fBdie\fP \fIERRNO\fP \fIMESSAGE\fP...
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBdie\fP prints each \fIMESSAGE\fP to standard error, formatted like so:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
*dying*: _MESSAGE_
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
and then exits with the \fIERRNO\fP given.
.sp
If colors are enabled (see idioms(3)), then "dying" will be red and emboldened.
